  "prompt": "What is 6 B in an O?",
  "response": "\"6 B in an O\" is a common riddle or abbreviation where each letter represents the first letter of a word in a phrase. In this case:\n\n**6 B in an O = 6 Balls in an Over**\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- **B** stands for **Balls**\n- **O** stands for **Over**\n\nIn the sport of **cricket**, an **over** consists of **six legal deliveries** (balls) bowled by a bowler. After six balls, the over is completed, and another bowler typically takes over from the opposite end of the pitch.\n\n**Example in a Sentence:**\n\n- \"He bowled a perfect **over**, delivering all **6 balls** without any extras.\"\n\nIf you have any more riddles or questions, feel free to ask!",
